          <span class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm">13 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          The Complete Guide to Tire Shop Marketing in Canada
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
          Escape the seasonal chaos. Build systems that spread demand, retain storage customers, and create year-round revenue.
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
          <span>Updated February 2026</span>
          <span class="mx-3">â€¢</span>
          <span>Lead Flow North Team</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- Featured Image -->
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-cyan-600 rounded-2xl h-64 md:h-96 flex items-center justify-center">
          <div class="text-center text-white">
            <div class="text-6xl mb-4">ðŸ›ž</div>
            <div class="text-xl font-semibold">Tire Shop Marketing Strategies</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
          
          <p class="lead text-xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
            Canadian tire shops face a unique challenge: extreme seasonal demand. October and November are chaos; January is dead. The shops that thrive have figured out how to spread that demand, retain customers year-round, and compete against the Costcos and Walmarts of the world.
          </p>

          <p>
            This guide will show you how to build systems that create predictable revenue, keep storage customers loyal, and turn seasonal chaos into manageable growth.
          </p>

          <!-- Table of Contents -->
          <div class="bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-xl my-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4 mt-0">What You'll Learn</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-2 mb-0">
              <li><a href="#seasonal" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Managing Seasonal Demand</a></li>
              <li><a href="#storage" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Retaining Storage Customers</a></li>
              <li><a href="#year-round" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Building Year-Round Revenue</a></li>
              <li><a href="#competing" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Competing with Big Box Stores</a></li>
              <li><a href="#reviews" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Building Your Online Reputation</a></li>
              <li><a href="#automation" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Automating Customer Communication</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h2 id="seasonal" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Managing Seasonal Demand</h2>

          <p>
            The secret to surviving seasonal chaos isn't working harder during peak weeksâ€”it's spreading demand across more weeks. Early-bird campaigns are your best tool.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">The Early-Bird Strategy</h3>

          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-xl my-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Fall Changeover Campaign Timeline:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 mb-0">
              <li><strong>September 1:</strong> "Beat the rush! Book your winter tire changeover nowâ€”priority scheduling"</li>
              <li><strong>September 15:</strong> "Early-bird special: Free storage inspection with changeover"</li>
              <li><strong>October 1:</strong> "Winter is comingâ€”secure your spot before the rush"</li>
              <li><strong>October 15:</strong> "Last chance for early bookingâ€”peak season starts soon"</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <p>
            The goal: move 30-40% of your seasonal appointments earlier in the season, when you have capacity. Incentives like priority scheduling or free services work better than discounts.
          </p>

          <h2 id="storage" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Retaining Storage Customers</h2>

          <p>
            Storage customers are your most valuable asset. They're locked in for both seasonal changeovers and have an ongoing relationship with you. But they're also the most likely to forget about you.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Storage Customer Communication Sequence</h3>

          <ol>
            <li><strong>Season end:</strong> Thank you + confirmation of storage + date reminder</li>
            <li><strong>Mid-season:</strong> "Your tires are safe! Here's what we inspected"</li>
            <li><strong>3 weeks before changeover season:</strong> "Time to book your changeoverâ€”early appointments available"</li>
            <li><strong>1 week before season:</strong> "Confirm your appointmentâ€”book now before we fill up"</li>
          </ol>

          <h2 id="year-round" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Building Year-Round Revenue</h2>

          <p>
            The tire business isn't just seasonal. Rotation reminders, alignment services, and tire replacement opportunities exist year-round.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Rotation Reminder System</h3>

          <p>
            Most customers should rotate tires every 8,000-12,000km. Track mileage at every visit and send automated reminders:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>Reminder at 500km before rotation due</li>
            <li>Easy online booking link</li>
            <li>Alignment upsell opportunity</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="competing" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Competing with Big Box Stores</h2>

          <p>
            You can't compete on price with Costco. But you can compete on convenience, expertise, and relationship:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Convenience:</strong> Online booking, quick turnaround, no membership required</li>
            <li><strong>Expertise:</strong> Proper balancing, TPMS service, alignment capabilities</li>
            <li><strong>Relationship:</strong> They know your name, your car, your preferences</li>
            <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Costco doesn't store your tiresâ€”you do</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="reviews" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Building Your Online Reputation</h2>

          <p>
            When someone searches "tire shop near me," reviews determine where they go. Every service visit is a review opportunity.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Review Request Timing</h3>

          <p>
            Request reviews same-day, while the experience is fresh. For tire shops, the best moment is right after pickup when they're driving on fresh tires.
          </p>

          <h2 id="automation" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Automating Customer Communication</h2>

          <p>
            During peak season, you don't have time to manually send reminders, follow up on bookings, or request reviews. Automation handles it all.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Essential Automated Sequences</h3>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Seasonal campaign:</strong> Early-bird reminders starting 6 weeks before peak</li>
            <li><strong>Appointment confirmations:</strong> Immediate booking confirmation + reminders</li>
            <li><strong>Storage reminders:</strong> Mid-season check-in + changeover booking prompts</li>
            <li><strong>Post-service:</strong> Thank you + review request + rotation reminder setup</li>
            <li><strong>Rotation reminders:</strong> Mileage-based follow-ups</li>
          </ul>

          <!-- CTA Box -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-cyan-600 p-8 rounded-xl text-white my-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Ready to Automate Your Tire Shop?</h3>
            <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6">
              Get a free consultation and see exactly how we'd implement these systems for your business.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 text-blue-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 transition">
              Book Your Free Demo
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
